The U.S. Environmental ProtectionAgency said it denied a request by Wheeling-Pittsburgh SteelCorp that it be allowed to continue to operate the Follansbee,W. Va., sinter plant while court-ordered pollution controlequipment is installed.    The EPA said that since the original consent decree withthe company was signed in 1979, the company had had numerousopportunities to reduce harmful emmissions from the plant.    The agency said that only after the company failed tocomply by the last available extension of its compliancedeadline did the agency ask the court to close the plant. Reuter&#3;